{"TopicId":187814,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Need guidance in understanding how to setup a relay network.","CreatedByName":"catloverjerrygarcia","CreatedById":171766,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-29T07:31:42Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"catloverjerrygarcia","CreatedById":171766,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-29T07:31:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have a relay satellite design set to go, but my knowledge of how to setup a network is absolute zero on the Kelvin scale.\u00A0 Have a look at my relay satellite design below and the launch assembly will be changed as needed to achieve the mission.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://flic.kr/p/2h7dPsv\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 alt=\u002248640800797_73d6f71816_h.jpg\u0022 src=\u0022https://live.staticflickr.com/65535/48640800797_73d6f71816_h.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://flic.kr/p/2h7dPsv\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EKerbinsat relay satellite.\u003C/a\u003E by \u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.flickr.com/photos/183843241@N08/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EAdmFranzvonHippie\u003C/a\u003E, on Flickr\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"VoidSquid","CreatedById":196199,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-29T08:13:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBasically you want to setup a comm network like this:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Tutorial:Setting_up_a_CommNet_system\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022 style=\u0022background-color:transparent;color:#3d6594;\u0022\u003Ehttps://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Tutorial:Setting_up_a_CommNet_system\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\nBe aware that you\u0027ll need Relay capable antennas:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Parts#Communications\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022 style=\u0022background-color:transparent;color:#4588c5;\u0022\u003Ehttps://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Parts#Communications\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\nTutorial - How to Create a Satellite Network with Evenly Spaced Satellites:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022173518\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed9368762341\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/161180-tutorial-how-to-create-a-satellite-network-with-evenly-spaced-satellites/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022background-color:#fcfcfc;border:1px solid rgba(0,0,0,.1);color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\nResonant Orbit Calculator:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://meyerweb.com/eric/ksp/resonant-orbits/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022 style=\u0022background-color:transparent;color:#3d6594;\u0022\u003Ehttps://meyerweb.com/eric/ksp/resonant-orbits/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\n...or in-game as a mod:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022129964\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed4324350846\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/177833-151-161-172-ksp-resonant-orbit-calculator/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022background-color:#fcfcfc;border:1px solid rgba(0,0,0,.1);color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs for your rocket, I suggest you build something with an payload like this, i.e. 3 satellites, each having a probe core, battery,\u00A0 reaction wheel, solar panels, fuel, small maneuver engine with a decoupler below:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022screenshot3-png-Windows-Photo-Viewer-201\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022241.37\u0022 height=\u0022768\u0022 width=\u0022318\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/CvtCtSh/screenshot3-png-Windows-Photo-Viewer-2019-08-24-09-48-16.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-08-29T08:20:42Z\u0022 title=\u002208/29/2019 08:20  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 29, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by VoidSquid\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-29T09:09:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou need to answer a question first. Do you want:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Col\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nA functional satellite network that may occasionally have a gap in coverage, but will facilitate most any reasonable expectation?\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nA perfectly symmetrical network with no gaps that works 100% of the time from everywhere?\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ol\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\nAll 1 takes is you to luanch a half dozen or so satellites into different orbits. One or two should be polar, and eccentric orbits going every which way chaotically is better than symmetry. If you\u0027re in career mode, just completing \u0022launch a satellite\u0022 contracts with relay antennas on the satellites is really all you need to do.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n[snip]\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-08-29T18:18:15Z\u0022 title=\u002208/29/2019 06:18  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 29, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by Vanamonde\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"dire","CreatedById":12239,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-29T10:17:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n[snip]\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s easy to feel overwhelmed by all the numbers and stuff. This is rocket science; it\u0027s a little bit difficult.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy advice would be to take it a step at a time. Launch your satellite and see what happens! It will have gaps in coverage.That\u0027s OK. You may lose probes if they go dark during a critical maneuver. That\u0027s also OK. As you launch more satellites and build better stuff you can come back to these topics several times and learn more each time.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOne of the things VoidSquid\u0027s picture is trying to say is that generally it\u0027s better to have several small, cheap relay satellites than one big one, all in different orbits. The reason why this is, is complicated, but try it out and see what happens.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-08-29T18:19:56Z\u0022 title=\u002208/29/2019 06:19  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 29, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by Vanamonde\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"VoidSquid","CreatedById":196199,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-29T10:21:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223662437\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187814\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221567073859\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002212239\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022dire\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, dire said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOne of the things VoidSquid\u0027s picture is trying to say is that generally it\u0027s better to have several small, cheap relay satellites than one big one, all in different orbits\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nActually I was thinking about the classic triangle constellation here, polar and / or equatorial, for the best possible coverage \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"dire","CreatedById":12239,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-29T10:31:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n[snip]\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTry this video where Scott Manley goes through it step by step. If you want a wall of text I can type something up, but try the video first.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022 data-embed-src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/EWFHiLUE2Ig?feature=oembed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022 data-embed-src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/w91Yiwpdmq8?feature=oembed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-08-29T18:20:21Z\u0022 title=\u002208/29/2019 06:20  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 29, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by Vanamonde\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vanamonde","CreatedById":27914,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-29T18:21:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSome off-topic and fairly harsh comments have been removed from this thread. Please stick to the subject and try to remember that people are trying to be helpful even if it\u0027s not in the form that works best for you.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}